@startuml seq_auth_registration
!theme plain
title Sequence Diagram: User Registration & OTP Verification

skinparam maxMessageSize 150

actor "New User" as User
participant "React SPA" as Client
participant "Kong API Gateway" as Gateway
participant "Auth Service" as Auth
database "Redis (Cache)" as Redis
participant "SMTP Server" as Email
database "PostgreSQL (HA)" as PG

== Phase 1: Request Registration ==
User -> Client : Submit Form (Username, Password, Email)
Client -> Gateway : POST /api/auth/register
Gateway -> Auth : Route Request (Rate Limited)

Auth -> Auth : Validate Input & Hash Password (Bcrypt)
Auth -> Auth : Generate 6-digit OTP
Auth -> Redis : SET otp:<email> with TTL (5 minutes)
Auth -> Email : Send OTP via Nodemailer
Email -> User : Deliver Email to Inbox
Auth -> Client : 200 OK (OTP Sent)

== Phase 2: OTP Verification ==
User -> Client : Input 6-digit OTP
Client -> Gateway : POST /api/auth/verify-otp
Gateway -> Auth : Route Request

Auth -> Redis : GET otp:<email>
Redis --> Auth : Return OTP String
Auth -> Auth : Compare OTPs
Auth -> PG : INSERT INTO users (status = 'PENDING_ADMIN')
Auth -> Client : 201 Created (Account Created)
Client -> User : Show Success & Redirect to Login
@enduml